CCI-JLC Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

CCI Analytics

4/13/2020

Detailed EDA - Part 2

Overview

Procedure: Analyze each feature (aka column) in the ‘Job_MST’ dataset. We are interested in the following:

  • Data Type
  • Zeros/Infinite Values/NA
  • Missing Values
  • Basic Trends
  • Unique/repeated values
  • Understanding each feature’s purpose

Each feature section has an obervations field as well as follow up questions that need to be answered to better our understanding of the data.

As this dataset is quite large, the features have been grouped together based on the number of unique values they house. This will help in keeping this EDA section organized and focused.

This dataset includes over 100 features (columns) and 10,000 rows.

Feature Distribution

As mentioned above, the features have been grouped together based on unique values.

Grouping Breakout:
- G1 -> features with unique values > 100
- G2 -> features with 10 > unique values <= 100
- G3 -> features with 1 > unique values <= 10
- G4 -> features with only 1 unique value

Groupings are by most unique features to least unique features. Meaning G1 are the most unique features in the dataset, while G4 are the least unique. Further more, any features realted to time are analyzed separately at the end.
